summary: Arya Stark drabble thing Secret By The Pierces, please!
question: Arya Stark drabble thing Secret By The Pierces, please!
answer:
Characters: Reader x Arya Stark
Warnings: Mentions of death
Lyric: “Why do you smile / Like you have told a secret”
Word Count: 381
A/N: Hope it’s okay!

NOT TAKING ANYMORE REQUESTS!

To be reunited with Arya again felt like a dream come true – sometimes you still struggled to believe she was really here, with you in Winterfell. You had spent so long believing she was dead, as so many others had convinced you she was, and while you refused to believe it at first, you slowly became to accept that it was a very real possibility.

You hadn’t expected Arya to be the same, mischievous girl you had once fooled around with in the Winterfell courtyards, but there was something about her that had changed so dramatically it almost felt as though she was a stranger. There was an aura of mystery surrounding her, lips curled into a smile as if she knew something bigger than all of you, a secret she refused to tell anyone. She lurked around the towers, her footsteps silent, often frightening you as she’d approach you from behind without even noticing.

And then there was her fighting skills. You had always known Arya was a fighter, but you had seen her spar with Brienne with Sansa. Arya was precise, quick, deadly – that wasn’t something she could’ve learned by herself.

“Who taught you how to do that?” Brienne had asked, and you couldn’t forget the smile Arya had flashed Brienne.

“No one.” she had replied, without missing a beat.

Arya had asked you about what had happened to you after Ned was executed, and you had so easily told her, your stories spilling from your lips before you realized she had never told you how she had survived, where she had gone. You had asked her multiple times, desperate to know where she had been, yet she remained elusive, her answers vague, clearly hiding something from you.

You didn’t know what she could be hiding. What had happened to the youngest Stark girl, and who had she become?

“What are you hiding from me, Arya?” you demanded one day, and Arya simply smiled, as if amused by your confusion. “Why won’t you tell me where you’ve been all this time?”

Arya didn’t respond, simply looking out as the snow quietly floated down onto every possible surface below, a white blanket over Winterfell. You would never believe her even if she told you. She took a deep breath, “Nowhere.”

summary: Can people stop pretending that everything a nine year old says is the gospel truth that will never change?  Just because Arya...
body: Can people stop pretending that everything a nine year old says is the gospel truth that will never change? Just because Arya doesn’t want to be a lady doesn’t mean she’s swearing off romance, sex, and potential marriage forever. It just means she doesn’t want to be sold off like a broodmare to some Lord that would control every aspect of her life from there on out. So yeah can people stop treating Arya like she’s a emotionless, non-gendered, asexual being whose only purpose is to be a sword? That would be really great, thanks
